fields.name: Garlic Head Each
fields.description:
Bulb made up of segments called cloves, covered by a papery shell. The most common varieties of garlic contain 10 cloves (or segments) with white skin. Other varieties have pink or purple skin and larger cloves. As a rule, the smaller the clove, the stronger the taste. 
It is a member of the allium family that also includes onions, chives, shallots, spring onions and leeks.

What to look for
Look for firm well-shaped cloves. Buy in small amounts and break off the cloves only when needed. Garlic dries out once detached. bulb of garlic has had its roots trimmed, one at a time. Garlic is never labelled since it sheds its skin if a label is applied to it.

Availability
All year.

Store
Keep in a cool dry place away from the sunlight. Avoid placing in plastic bags, or storing in the refrigerator or everything in the refrigerator will end up tasting of garlic. Avoid storing next to ginger as ginger dehydrates garlic.

How to prepare
Separate cloves from bulbs, remove papery skin unless roasting when skin can be left on. Cut bulbs in half crosswise and brush with oil to roast. To remove skin, press the clove under the flat side of a knife and the skin will come off easily. Chop the garlic very finely or crush it with the side of a knife. Alternatively, use a garlic crusher.

Ways to eat
Garlic can be eaten raw or cooked. Raw garlic produces a strong, pungent flavour while cooking gives a more mellow flavour. The longer garlic is cooked, the milder and sweeter the flavour. It's usually used in small amounts, 2-3 cloves to a dish. Garlic burns easily, so take care when frying or sauteing. It can be used in vegetable dishes, meats, soups, dips, stir fries, braises and stews. Add whole unpeeled cloves into a roasting pan with meat or vegetables. Cut a whole head in half horizontally and roast in a little olive oil. When cooked, serve as it is, or squeeze the roasted flesh out and serve on crostini or fresh bread.

Cooking Methods
Roast, braise, stew, stir fry.

Our farms are independently audited, so you can feel confident that the hens laying your eggs are well cared for, and only the best quality golden-yolked Free Range eggs make it to your table to Make Every Day Sunny! fields.name: Chicken and Vegetable Stir-Fry with Rice
fields.description: This Chicken and Vegetable Stir-Fry is a quick and nutritious meal perfect for bulking. Tender chicken breast is stir-fried with a colorful mix of vegetables and coated in a savory blend of soy and hoisin sauces. Served over a bed of fluffy rice, this dish provides a balanced combination of protein, fiber, and carbohydrates, making it ideal for a satisfying and energy-boosting lunch.
instructions: Heat 15 milliliters of olive oil in a large skillet or wok over medium-high heat.
Add the minced garlic and ginger to the skillet. Cook for about 1 minute, or until fragrant, stirring frequently to prevent burning.
Add the chicken pieces to the skillet. Cook for 5-7 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the chicken is browned and cooked through (internal temperature should reach 75C or 165F).
Add the mixed vegetables to the skillet with the chicken. Continue to stir-fry for an additional 3-5 minutes, or until the vegetables are tender-crisp.
Stir in 15 milliliters of soy sauce and 7.5 milliliters of hoisin sauce. Cook for another 2-3 minutes, ensuring that the chicken and vegetables are evenly coated with the sauce.
Taste and adjust seasoning with salt and pepper if needed.
Serve the chicken and vegetable stir-fry over 150 grams of cooked rice.

fields.name: Salmon Teriyaki with Rice
fields.description: This Salmon Teriyaki with Rice is a simple yet delicious high-protein meal perfect for bulking. The salmon is coated in a sweet and savory teriyaki glaze and baked to perfection. Served alongside rice and optionally paired with steamed asparagus or green beans, this dish is both nutritious and satisfying, making it a great choice for lunch.
instructions: Preheat the oven to 190C (375F). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper for easy cleanup.
In a small bowl, mix 30 milliliters of teriyaki sauce with 10 milliliters of honey until well combined.
Place the salmon fillet on the lined baking sheet. Brush the top of the salmon evenly with the teriyaki and honey mixture, making sure it's well coated.

Place the baking sheet in the preheated oven and bake the salmon for 15-20 minutes, or until the salmon is cooked through and flakes easily with a fork (internal temperature should reach 63C or 145F).
While the salmon is baking, steam 100 grams of asparagus or green beans until tender. This step is optional but adds extra nutrients to the meal.
Once the salmon is done, serve it over 150 grams of cooked white or brown rice.
Optionally, place the steamed vegetables on the side.
Garnish with sesame seeds for extra flavor and presentation.

fields.name: Special Cancer Egg
fields.description: This dish is special edition established from seasoned 1103's chef. The texture of the crispy egg blend with the hot sensation of sambal is a perfect combination to fulfill your feast.
instructions: In a medium bowl, crack the eggs and add seasoning with salt and pepper.
Whisk the mixture until the yolks and whites are fully combined and slightly frothy.
Place a frying pot over high heat.
Add the oil to the pot until approximately the egg can be covered perfectly with the oil.
Once the oil is hot (it should shimmer), pour the egg mixture into the pot slowly.
As you pour, create a gentle swirl in the oil to help the omelette get crispy.
Cook the omelette until the bottom is golden brown and crispy, about 2-3 minutes.
Carefully flip the omelette using a spatula and cook the other side until it's also golden brown.
Once both sides are cooked, take the omelette out of the oil and let it drain on a paper towel to remove excess oil.
Serve the omelette over a bed of cooked rice.
Top with sambal for added flavor and spice.

fields.name: Grilled Chicken Teriyaki with Jasmine Rice
fields.description: This savory meal features marinated grilled chicken glazed with a rich teriyaki sauce, served alongside fluffy jasmine rice. The combination of the juicy, tender chicken and the aromatic rice creates a satisfying dish that is both delicious and filling. Perfect for a quick weeknight dinner, this meal is packed with protein to keep you energized throughout your day.
instructions: Cook the Jasmine rice according to package instructions (1 cup rice to 2 cups water).
Marinate the chicken thigh fillets in Ayam Teriyaki Sauce, grated ginger, and minced garlic for 30 minutes.
Heat oil in a pan, grill the marinated chicken on medium heat for 6-8 minutes on each side until fully cooked.
Steam the mixed vegetables for 3-5 minutes or until tender.
Serve the grilled chicken with rice and vegetables on the side

fields.name: Hoisin Tofu Stir-Fry with Rice
fields.description: Dive into a delightful blend of crispy tofu stir-fried with a mix of colorful vegetables, all tossed in a savory hoisin sauce. Served with steamed rice, this vegetarian dish offers a wonderful combination of textures and flavors. Its an excellent source of plant-based protein and is sure to satisfy both vegetarians and meat-lovers alike with its bold taste.
instructions: Cook the Jasmine rice.
ut the tofu into cubes and marinate in Ayam Hoisin Sauce for 15 minutes.
Heat Ohlio Canola Oil in a pan and stir-fry the marinated tofu until crispy on all sides.
Add minced garlic, grated ginger, and mixed vegetables to the pan and stir-fry for another 5 minutes.
Serve the tofu stir-fry with rice and sprinkle with sesame seeds.

fields.name: Honey Glazed Salmon with Rice and Vegetables
fields.description: This meal showcases tender salmon fillets glazed with a sweet honey sauce, complemented by a side of jasmine rice and sauted vegetables. The balance of sweetness from the honey and the freshness of the vegetables creates a delightful dish that is both satisfying and healthy. Ideal for pescatarians looking to enjoy a hearty meal without compromising on flavor.
instructions: Marinate the salmon fillets in honey, minced garlic, salt, and pepper for 20 minutes.
Cook the Jasmine rice as per the package instructions.
Heat Ohlio Canola Oil in a pan and cook the salmon fillets for 4-5 minutes on each side until golden and cooked.
Steam the mixed vegetables and serve alongside the salmon and rice.

fields.name: Spiced Grilled Chicken with Quinoa Salad
fields.description: A flavorful and nutritious meal featuring marinated grilled chicken breast served over a refreshing quinoa salad. This dish combines the wholesome goodness of protein-rich chicken with the lightness of fresh vegetables and quinoa, making it perfect for a healthy meal. It's easy to prepare and offers a delightful balance of spices that enhance the natural flavors of the ingredients.
instructions: Preheat the grill. Rub the chicken breasts with olive oil, minced garlic, cumin, paprika, salt, and black pepper. Grill for 6-8 minutes on each side or until fully cooked.
Rinse the quinoa under cold water. Boil 200ml water, add the quinoa, and simmer for 15 minutes until the water is absorbed.
In a bowl, combine the cucumber, cherry tomatoes, red onion, and cooked quinoa.
Drizzle the lemon juice and 20ml of olive oil over the salad. Garnish with parsley and season with salt.
Serve the grilled chicken on top of the quinoa salad.

fields.name: Zucchini Noodles with Pesto
fields.description: This vibrant dish features spiralized zucchini noodles tossed in a creamy vegan pesto made from fresh basil and pine nuts. It's a refreshing, light meal that highlights the natural flavors of vegetables and is perfect for those looking to enjoy a low-carb, gluten-free option. The recipe is simple to prepare, making it an ideal choice for a quick and healthy dinner.
instructions: Spiralize the zucchini into noodles and set aside.
In a blender or food processor, combine the basil, pine nuts, garlic, olive oil, lemon juice, nutritional yeast (if using), salt, and pepper. Blend until smooth.
Lightly saut the zucchini noodles in a pan for 2-3 minutes.
Toss the noodles in the pesto and serve immediately.

fields.name: Lemon Garlic Shrimp with Couscous
fields.description: A delightful combination of succulent shrimp sauted in a zesty lemon garlic sauce, served over fluffy couscous. This meal is quick to prepare and bursting with flavor, making it an ideal choice for seafood lovers. The fresh ingredients create a light yet satisfying dish, perfect for a busy weeknight dinner.
instructions: Bring 200ml of water to a boil and pour it over the couscous in a bowl. Cover and let it steam for 5 minutes, then fluff with a fork.
In a pan, heat the olive oil and saut the garlic for 1 minute. Add the shrimp and cook for 2-3 minutes until they turn pink.
Add the lemon zest and juice to the pan and toss the shrimp to coat. Season with salt and pepper.
Serve the shrimp on a bed of couscous and garnish with parsley.

fields.name: Vegetable Frittata
fields.description: This hearty vegetable frittata is a protein-packed dish filled with colorful vegetables and eggs. It's a versatile recipe that can be enjoyed for breakfast, lunch, or dinner. The combination of fresh ingredients and a fluffy egg base makes it a satisfying meal that's both nutritious and delicious.
instructions: Preheat the oven to 180C. Heat olive oil in a pan and saut the onion, red bell pepper, and spinach until soft.
In a bowl, whisk the eggs and season with salt and pepper.
Pour the egg mixture over the sauted vegetables in an oven-safe pan.
Optionally, sprinkle nutritional yeast on top for a cheesy flavor.
Bake the frittata for 12-15 minutes, or until the eggs are set.
Slice and serve.

fields.name: Beef Stir-Fry with Bell Peppers
fields.description: This vibrant beef stir-fry is packed with colorful bell peppers and full of flavor. A quick and nutritious dish that highlights tender beef strips sauted with fresh vegetables, it's perfect for a paleo diet. This stir-fry is not only delicious but also a great way to get your daily dose of protein and vitamins.
instructions: Heat olive oil in a large pan or wok over medium heat. Add the beef strips and cook for 4-5 minutes, until browned.
Add the garlic, onion, and bell peppers and stir-fry for another 3-4 minutes.
Pour in the coconut aminos and season with salt and pepper. Stir-fry for another 2 minutes.
Serve immediately.

fields.name: Lentil and Vegetable Stew
fields.description: This hearty lentil and vegetable stew is a comforting, wholesome dish brimming with flavor. Packed with protein-rich lentils and a variety of vegetables, this stew is not only filling but also nutritious. It's perfect for a cozy dinner and can be made in large batches for meal prep.
instructions: In a large pot, heat olive oil and saut the onion, carrot, and celery for 5-7 minutes until softened.
Add garlic, cumin, and thyme, cooking for another minute.
Stir in the red lentils, canned tomatoes, and vegetable broth. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 20-25 minutes until the lentils are tender.
Season with salt and pepper before serving.

fields.name: Bulk-Up Power Meal Kit
fields.description: The Bulk-Up Power Meal Kit is designed for individuals aiming to increase muscle mass while enjoying delicious, nutrient-dense meals. This meal kit includes two high-protein recipes: Chicken and Vegetable Stir-Fry with Rice and Salmon Teriyaki with Rice. Both dishes feature a balanced combination of lean protein, wholesome vegetables, and satisfying rice, ensuring you're fueled with the right nutrients to support muscle growth and recovery. Each meal is simple to prepare, making it perfect for those with busy lifestyles but still looking to meet their fitness goals.

fields.description: This richly flavoured honey has been sourced from select international honeys and then expertly blended with delicious, delicate Australian honey. fields.name: Sunny Queen 12 Extra Large Free Range Eggs 700g
fields.description: Our smiley Free Range eggs are laid by happy country hens on farms with a maximum outdoor density of 1500 hens per hectare. That's over 6 times more space than the Australian National Free Range Standard Limit and lots of room to roam, peck and play with their friends during the day! At night they sleep inside where they are safe from other animals and harsh weather. Our farms are independently audited, so you can feel confident that the hens laying your eggs are well cared for, and only the best quality golden-yolked Free Range eggs make it to your table to Make Every Day Sunny! All our eggs come in 100% biodegradable and compostable egg cartons. We're proudly farmed by Aussie families with over 50 years of eggs-perience delivering nutritious food from our farms to your table.

fields.name: Red Bell Pepper 220g
fields.description: The colour of a capsicum is indicative of when it was harvested with the stages of ripeness transcending from green, yellow, orange through to red. All are edible however the colours also indicate the levels of sweetness and as red capsicums are the most mature, they are the sweetest and contain the most Vitamin C. Due to their almost fruity sweet flavour, this is the best to eat fresh or pack in kids lunchboxes.
